main event: A fast-moving, circular object was observed by military officers in southeast Oregon, emitting a bright light that illuminated the entire area around it.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 10 minutes before disappearing from sight.
The object was estimated to be the size of a large automobile and at an altitude of 10,000 feet.
The object moved at a high rate of speed, estimated to be around 800 mph.
The object had a reddish-orange color with a white center spot.
The sighting duration was approximately 15-20 seconds.
